// Enhanced escrow with collateral and time limit
// Case study 1 — matches §4 of the architecture paper
//
// Party A wants to buy 500 WETH from Party B.
// Party A locks 1000 USDC as collateral to ensure they follow through.
// Party B must deliver the WETH within 30 days.
// On delivery, the locked USDC is released to Party A (they need it to pay).

Party A locks 1000 USDC as collateral for Party B.
Party B must transfer 500 WETH to Party A within 30 days.
if price of WETH rises above 2500 USD, Party A receives 1000 USDC from vault.
